    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 79.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Kanagawa,
                                    Yokohama</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 1, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The government have agreed to pay the sum
                            of $10,000, being the bill of damages presented by Russell &amp; Co.,
                            for the interruption of the voyage of the Pembroke.</p>
                <p>Satsuma has not paid British indemnity, though eight days overdue;
                            explanations have been asked from Gorogio.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in
                                    Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
